# Planning & docs — run the build through Atlassian (MCP)

The build is plan-first. Jira is the backlog and system of record; Confluence is the living
design docs. Full backlog + space layout: `docs/PLAN.md`.

**Two interfaces, different jobs** (see `docs/TEAMWORK-SKILLS.md`):
- **Atlassian MCP** — for deterministic *writes* in the build loop: create/transition/comment/
  link a story, create/update a Confluence page. This is the default for `/start-ticket` and
  `/ship-ticket`.
- **`twg` skills** (`~/.claude/skills/twg*`, scanned by Cursor) — reach for the *narrowest* one
  when you need *synthesis/discovery* over work-data: `twg-context-discovery` ("catch me up" /
  project-to-repo), `twg-engineering-work` (PR/review queues), `twg-operational-health`
  (incident review), `twg-status-rollups` (leadership rollup). Resolve IDs first; scope to the
  **PIG** project / **Pigment** space; never guess keys.

## Every build task starts from a Jira story
- **Pull first.** Before writing code for a phase, `getJiraIssue` (or `searchJiraIssuesUsingJql`
  for the next To Do story in epic PIG). Read the acceptance criteria and the linked Confluence
  page. Never start from a blank prompt when a story exists.
- **Plan back.** Post your Plan-mode plan as a comment with `addCommentToJiraIssue`, then move
  the story to In Progress with `transitionJiraIssue` (look up valid transitions first with
  `getTransitionsForJiraIssue`).

## As you build
- Keep the story honest: log effort with `addWorklogToJiraIssue`; comment material decisions or
  blockers.
- **Write decisions to Confluence.** Append a short ADR (what you chose + why) to the
  **Decision Log** page via `updateConfluencePage`, and update the **Design System Spec** /
  **SDLC Pipeline** page if the phase changed it.

## On completion
- Link the PR to the story with `createIssueLink`; transition the story to Done.
- A production fix (from Sentry) is a NEW story — create it with `createJiraIssue` in epic PIG,
  don't reopen the shipped one.

## Guardrails
- Scope strictly to the **PIG** Jira project and **Pigment** Confluence space. Never read or
  write other projects/spaces.
- Never invent issue keys or page IDs — always create/look up via the MCP and use the returned
  identifiers.
- This is a real Teamwork site: prefer comments/ADRs over editing acceptance criteria; don't
  delete issues or pages.
